text: This movie makes me so sad with the endless amounts of missed potential. It could have been SO good! Unfortunately, it was crippled by not only a needlessly convoluted subplot that went nowhere, (in an effort to set up for a string of sequels) but also by a PG13 rating. If it had been rated R, and the producers had green lighted the amount of blood, gore, and violence that a TRUE vampire flick needs to shine, it would have been amazing.  That being said, I loved this movie. The casting was great, the acting was actually surprisingly good, the special effects were fucking gorgeous, and the music was absolutely beautiful. Not to mention, that the action beats that we DID get, were absolutely awesome.  A solid part of my love for this movie is probably my absolute obsession with Vampires. But hey, we all have our little problems.  And before any of you say anything, I said Vampires, not sparkly fey creatures that glitter in the sun.

text: Not a bad movie. A bit cheesy, but I was glad that this time they managed to get a bit closer to Vlad's real story (except for vampirism of course;)). I really recommend you read about Vlad Tepes' real life, it's quite heartbreaking, but powerful, motivating almost. He was a real life tragic hero and so misunderstood by many.  Oh and he didn't really want to "rule the world", rather Walachia and the other Romanian provinces that everybody was fighting to steal away. He also wanted vengeance, over his father's death, over his brother's death, over the immense betrayal around his family and country. Much like the Starks... ;)))
